      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WEFFALEE LEE LEE (1) boasts a strong record this journey with six wins and six minors from 13 tries. Below best last time at Nowra (20.82) in a NG, finishing a 9 length fourth. Appeals as a leading chance in this. HANK MCCOY (8) has missed the placings at his last two but was second at this track three back and returns to Maitland where he tends to run well. Speedy runner who can find the front with a clear break from out wide. This looks easier and expected to improve sharply. FREIGHT EXPRESS (5) was well backed last start but ran below expectations when fourth (22.93), beaten 7 lengths. Finished second the start before. Expected to feature in the finish. REGGAE ETHICS (2) gets a chance to improve on an unplaced run at his latest outing at this circuit.",
